n=2^k
\begin{align}T(2^k) &= 2^kk + 2\cdot 2^{k-1}(k-1) + 2^2\cdot2^{k-2}(k-2) + \cdots + 2^{k-2}\cdot 2^2 2 + 2^{k-1}2 \\ &= 2^k \sum _{j=1}^{k} j = 2^k\frac{k(k+1)}{2} = 2^{k-1}k(k+1)\quad \mathrel{\Big[=} O(n\log^2(n))\Big]\end{align}
